[DhtmlXQ_comment0]mg kunzi 01||Material advantage is often desicive in Xiangqi. One of the most basic tactics to learn is the tactic of containing your oppoenent's pieces, thereby allowing the capture of an opponent's major piece.||In this example, both sides have the same attacking pieces, 2h1c. Black has one more pawn and has a horse that is applying pressure. BUT, that horse is alone and black's right flank is relatively naked.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]preventing the horse from running away! ||All the possible escape routes of this horse is blocked off.||Red will now slowly capture it.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
[DhtmlXQ_comment2]To try to protect that trapped horse.[/DhtmlXQ_comment2]
[DhtmlXQ_comment5]Correct move to make!||Click on the variation below to understand why red cannot move C4+1[/DhtmlXQ_comment5]
[DhtmlXQ_comment9]Black's horse is red's now. Red enters the latter part of the midgame or early part of the endgame with a huge advantage.[/DhtmlXQ_comment9]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1_6]and the black horse will force an exchange with the red horse. Red has done much work...in vain.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1_6]
[DhtmlXQ_comment2_3]And the black horse is lost. Black cannot move the  cannon C3=7 to protect the horse as the red horse has that intersection covered too![/DhtmlXQ_comment2_3]
